# System Architecture — Dropout Signal

## Overview

Dropout Signal is a five-layer early warning system built entirely 
on Databricks. It detects student dropout risk weeks before it 
appears in grades, explains each prediction in plain English, and 
audits every output for demographic fairness.

The system is designed for two audiences simultaneously:
- Data teams who need a rigorous, fair, explainable ML pipeline
- School counselors who need plain English answers about which 
  students need help and why

---

## The core philosophy

Most student support systems ask: is this student at risk right now?

Dropout Signal asks: is this student's situation getting worse, 
and how fast?

This shift from snapshot to trajectory is what enables intervention 
weeks before dropout becomes inevitable. By the time a static system 
flags a student, the window for effective intervention has often 
already closed.

