## Layer 1 — Data Ingestion

Raw institutional data is ingested into Databricks and stored 
as versioned Delta tables in Unity Catalog.

### Data sources

| Source | What it contains |
|---|---|
| Academic records | GPA per student per week per semester |
| Attendance logs | Daily and weekly attendance per student |
| Financial records | Payment status, aid status, fee waivers |
| Engagement records | Counselor visits, club activity, library check-ins |

### Storage design

- All raw tables stored in Delta Lake
- Schema enforced at ingestion time
- Full data versioning handled automatically by Delta
- Time travel enabled — any historical state is queryable

### Why Delta Lake

Delta Lake gives us ACID transactions on top of cloud storage.
This matters because student data arrives from multiple systems 
at different times. Delta ensures we never have a partially 
updated table that could corrupt downstream features.

