## Layer 5 — Explainability

### The problem with global explanations

Standard feature importance says: attendance is the most important 
feature overall. That is a model-level statement. It helps nobody 
make a decision about a specific student.

We use SHAP to generate per-student explanations.

### How SHAP works here

SHAP values are computed for every student at every prediction.
The top 3 contributing features are extracted per student.
Feature names are mapped to plain English reason codes.

| SHAP feature | Reason shown to counselor |
|---|---|
| grade_slope_4w negative | Grades have been declining for 4 weeks |
| attendance_delta below -0.2 | Attendance dropped significantly below personal baseline |
| financial_stress_index above 0.7 | Ongoing financial pressure detected |
| engagement_recency above 30 | No school engagement in over 30 days |
| consecutive_late_payments above 1 | Multiple consecutive late payments |

### Why this matters

A counselor does not need to understand SHAP values.
They need to understand why the system flagged this specific student 
and what they should do about it.

The translation from model internals to plain English reason codes 
is what makes this system usable in the real world.

