## Layer 6 — Genie Space

### What it is

Databricks Genie is the natural language interface layer of this 
system. It allows school counselors and administrators to query 
student risk data in plain English — no SQL, no Python, no 
technical knowledge required.

This is the layer that transforms Dropout Signal from a model 
into a complete tool for the humans who make intervention decisions.

### Connected tables

| Table | What it contains |
|---|---|
| students_clean | Cleaned student profiles with demographic data |
| risk_scores | Model output — scores, bands, prediction dates |
| intervention_output | Final table with reasons and recommended actions |
| fairness_audit | Group level FPR and FNR audit results |

### Example questions counselors can ask

Academic risk:
- Show me all high risk students this week
- Which students have had declining grades for more than 3 weeks
- List students whose GPA dropped more than 0.5 points this semester

Attendance:
- Which students are attending 30% less than their personal baseline
- Who has the worst attendance trend in the last 4 weeks
- Show me students with more than 5 unexcused absences this month

Financial stress:
- Which students have a financial stress index above 0.7
- Show me students with two or more consecutive late payments
- List students whose financial aid status changed this semester

Engagement:
- Which students have not engaged in any activity for 30 days
- Show me students with high risk scores and zero engagement
- Who has both financial stress and declining attendance

Intervention management:
- How many students are in each risk band this week
- Which high risk students have not been contacted yet
- Show me all students assigned a counselor call this week
- List students where the fairness flag shows a review is needed

### Genie system prompt

The Genie Space is configured with this instruction:

You are a student risk assistant for school counselors.
Answer questions about student dropout risk clearly and concisely.
Always show student names, risk scores, and recommended actions.
Flag any students where fairness verification shows a review is needed.
Use plain English. Avoid technical jargon.
Prioritize students with the highest risk scores in every response.

### How to recreate the Genie Space

1. Open Databricks workspace
2. Click Genie in the left sidebar
3. Click Create new Genie Space
4. Name it: Dropout Signal — Student Risk Assistant
5. Connect the four tables listed above
6. Paste the system prompt above into the instructions field
7. Save and test with the example questions

