## Key design principles

Trend over snapshot
We do not ask where a student is. We ask where they are going.
Direction of change is more predictive than current level.

Personal baseline over population average
Every student is compared against their own history.
This catches individual deterioration regardless of starting point.

Fairness inside the pipeline
Fairness audit runs before output generation.
It is not an evaluation — it is a gate.

Counselor-first output
Every output is designed for a non-technical user.
Risk scores paired with plain English explanations.
Genie Space for natural language queries over live data.

Early over accurate
A prediction that is slightly less accurate but arrives 6 weeks 
earlier is more valuable than a highly accurate prediction that 
arrives after intervention is no longer possible.
